## Code conventions

- Python: `ruff format`, `ruff check`, type hints required
- TypeScript: prettier defaults, strict mode, no `any`
- Tests next to source: `*_test.py`, `*.test.ts`
- Conventional Commits: `feat(scope): description`, `fix(scope): description`, etc.

## Commit style

When you draft a commit message for Golden to use, write it as ordinary human dev voice. Examples:

GOOD:
- `feat(backend): add region promote endpoint with backup detection`
- `fix(jjscan): handle empty SYSLIB concatenation`
- `chore(mcp): wire helios-corpus server alongside cloudant`

BAD:
- ❌ Anything mentioning AI generation
- ❌ "Co-Authored-By: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>"
- ❌ "🤖 Generated with [Claude Code]" footer
- ❌ Overly verbose messages that read like AI output

